{
  "texts": [
    "Although RSD values, much like model performance, sharply improve after instruction-tuning, the resulting models' BiasScore is often higher than their base counterparts.",
    "Similarly, while RSD improves with scaling, the BiasScore of smaller models is lower.",
    "We note that higher performance together with lower RSD means that the model's performance has improved across most classes.",
    "In contrast, higher BiasScore indicates that its average predicted probabilities grew farther than uniform.",
    "Taken together, this implies that the scaled-up and instruction-tuned models are making more confident predictions on some classes, but not on others."
  ]
}